title: The Mutiny of the Bounty and Other Narratives
creator: William Bligh
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Mutiny of the Bounty and Other Narratives, by William Bligh. Read by John Greenman. In Bligh's own words, we hear about the lead-up to the famous mutiny and what happened afterwards with the mutineers and the castaways. This work contains two additional narratives by Bligh: Life of a Sailor Boy and The Sunken Treasure. (Summary by John Greenman) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (97MB)
